1.2 Define a common interface for batch correction methods

correct.batch.effects <- function(
    sce,
    method,
    batch='subject',
    celltype='celltype',
    BPPARAM=SerialParam()
    ){
  cat('Correcting batch effects by', method, '\n')
  batches <- colData(sce)[[batch]]
  celltypes <- colData(sce)[[celltype]]

  if (method == 'limma'){
    assay(sce, 'limma_logcounts') <- removeBatchEffect(logcounts(sce),
                                                       batch=batches,
                                                       batch2=celltypes)
  }else if (method == 'fastMNN'){
    out <- fastMNN(sce, batch=batches, BPPARAM=BPPARAM)
    assay(sce, 'fastMNN_logcounts') <- assay(out, 'reconstructed')

  }else if (method == 'combat'){
    assay(sce, "combat_counts") <- ComBat_seq(counts=as.matrix(counts(sce)),
                                              batch=batches,
                                              group=celltypes)
    sce <- logNormCounts(sce, assay.type='combat_counts', name='combat_logcounts', BPPARAM=BPPARAM)
  }else if (method == 'scMerge'){
    data("segList", package = "scMerge")
    scMerge_supervised <- scMerge(sce_combine = sce,
                                  ctl = segList$human$human_scSEG,
                                  assay_name = "scMerge_supervised",
                                  batch_name = batch,
                                  cell_type = celltypes,
                                  BPPARAM = BPPARAM)
    assay(sce, "scMerge_logcounts") <- assay(scMerge_supervised, "scMerge_supervised")
  }else if (method == 'scMerge2'){
    data("segList", package = "scMerge")
    exprsMat <- scMerge2(exprsMat = logcounts(sce),
                         batch = batches,
                         cellTypes = celltypes,
                         ctl = segList$human$human_scSEG)
    assay(sce, "scMerge2_logcounts") <- exprsMat$newY
  }else{
    stop(paste("Batch correction method", method, "not found."))
  }
  cat(method, 'correction finished.\n')
  return(sce)
}

1.3 Load scRNA-seq datasets

pbmc_lupus <- readRDS(file.path(load.path, "pbmc_lupus.rds"))
pbmc_covid <- readRDS(file.path(load.path, "pbmc_covid.rds"))

2 Run batch correction

for (bc.method in c('limma', 'fastMNN', 'combat', 'scMerge', 'scMerge2')){
  pbmc_lupus <- correct.batch.effects(pbmc_lupus, bc.method, 'subject', 'celltype', BPPARAM)
  pbmc_covid <- correct.batch.effects(pbmc_covid, bc.method, 'sampleID', 'majorType', BPPARAM)
}

saveRDS(pbmc_lupus, file.path(save.path, "pbmc_lupus_bc.rds"))
saveRDS(pbmc_covid, file.path(save.path, "pbmc_covid_bc.rds"))

3 Run PCA and UMAP

pbmc_lupus <- readRDS(file.path(save.path, "pbmc_lupus_bc.rds"))
pbmc_covid <- readRDS(file.path(save.path, "pbmc_covid_bc.rds"))

for (bc.method in c('origin', 'limma', 'fastMNN', 'combat', 'scMerge', 'scMerge2')){
  # create name of assay that stores corrected, PCA and UMAP data
  expr.assay.name <- ifelse(bc.method == 'origin', 'logcounts', paste(bc.method, 'logcounts', sep = '_'))
  pca.assay.name <- paste(bc.method, 'pca', sep='_')
  umap.assay.name <- paste(bc.method, 'umap', sep='_')
  
  cat('Start to compute principal components of', expr.assay.name, '\n')
  pbmc_lupus <- runPCA(pbmc_lupus, assay.type=expr.assay.name, name=pca.assay.name, subset_row=rownames(pbmc_lupus))
  pbmc_covid <- runPCA(pbmc_covid, assay.type=expr.assay.name, name=pca.assay.name, subset_row=rownames(pbmc_covid))
  cat('Principal components have been computed.\n')
  
  cat('Start to compute UMAP of', expr.assay.name, '\n')
  pbmc_lupus <- runUMAP(pbmc_lupus, dimred=pca.assay.name, name=umap.assay.name, BPPARAM=BPPARAM)
  pbmc_covid <- runUMAP(pbmc_covid, dimred=pca.assay.name, name=umap.assay.name, BPPARAM=BPPARAM)
  cat('UMAP have been computed.\n')
}

saveRDS(pbmc_lupus, file.path(save.path, "pbmc_lupus_bc_dr.rds"))
saveRDS(pbmc_covid, file.path(save.path, "pbmc_covid_bc_dr.rds"))

4.2 UMAP visualization

visualizeUMAP <- function(sce, celltype.rep, subject.rep){
  dr.arr.names <- reducedDimNames(sce)
  umap.arr.names <- dr.arr.names[endsWith(dr.arr.names, 'umap')]
  
  pic.list <- list()
  for (umap.name in umap.arr.names){
    pic.list[[paste(umap.name, subject.rep, sep='_')]] <- plotReducedDim(sce, dimred=umap.name, color_by=subject.rep, scattermore=TRUE, point_size=1)
    pic.list[[paste(umap.name, celltype.rep, sep='_')]] <- plotReducedDim(sce, dimred=umap.name, color_by=celltype.rep, scattermore=TRUE, point_size=1)
  }
  wrap_plots(pic.list, ncol=2)
}

visualizeUMAP(pbmc_lupus, celltype.rep='celltype', subject.rep='subject')

visualizeUMAP(pbmc_covid, celltype.rep='majorType', subject.rep='sampleID')

4.3 LISI computation

compute.LISI <- function(
    sce,
    pca.assay.name,
    batch='subject',
    celltype='celltype'
    ){
  stopifnot(pca.assay.name %in% reducedDimNames(sce))
  cat('Compute LISI metrics on PCs of', pca.assay.name, '...\n')
  lisi <- as.matrix(compute_lisi(reducedDim(sce, pca.assay.name), colData(sce), c(batch, celltype)))
  cat('Cell-level LISI values have been computed.\n')
  summary <- rbind(colMedians(lisi), colMins(lisi), colMaxs(lisi))
  normed.lisi <- (summary[1,] - summary[2,]) / (summary[3,] - summary[2,])
  lisi.res <- normed.lisi %>%
    `names<-`(c('batch', 'celltype')) %>%
    t() %>%
    as.data.frame(row.names = c(pca.assay.name)) %>%
    mutate(celltype = 1.0 - celltype,
           f1LISI = 2 * celltype * batch / (celltype + batch)) %>%
    rename(iLISI = batch, '1-cLISI' = celltype)
  cat('Summarized LISI values have been computed.\n\n')
  return(lisi.res)
}
bc.methods <- c('origin', 'limma', 'fastMNN', 'combat', 'scMerge', 'scMerge2')
pca.assay.names <- str_c(bc.methods, 'pca', sep='_')

lupus.lisi <- bplapply(pca.assay.names, compute.LISI, sce=pbmc_lupus, batch='subject', celltype='celltype') %>% bind_rows() %>% rownames_to_column('low_dim_rep')
covid.lisi <- bplapply(pca.assay.names, compute.LISI, sce=pbmc_covid, batch='sampleID', celltype='majorType') %>% bind_rows() %>% rownames_to_column('low_dim_rep')

write.csv(lupus.lisi, file.path(save.path, "pbmc_lupus_lisi.csv"), row.names = F)
write.csv(covid.lisi, file.path(save.path, "pbmc_covid_lisi.csv"), row.names = F)
lupus.lisi <- read_csv(file.path(save.path, "pbmc_lupus_lisi.csv"), show_col_types = FALSE) %>% mutate(dataset='PBMC-SLE')
covid.lisi <- read_csv(file.path(save.path, "pbmc_covid_lisi.csv"), show_col_types = FALSE) %>% mutate(dataset='PBMC-COVID19')

list(lupus.lisi, covid.lisi) %>% bind_rows() %>% 
  mutate(low_dim_rep=fct_reorder(low_dim_rep, desc(f1LISI))) %>%
  ggplot(aes(fill=dataset, y=f1LISI, x=low_dim_rep)) + 
    geom_bar(position="dodge", stat="identity")
